# Patch to mezmo_benchmark/config/aura-sregym.toml.template
#
# Adds a MANDATORY first-action instruction telling the agent to
# invoke load_skill(name="kubernetes-pod-triage") BEFORE any other
# tool call. Without this mandate, the agent registers the load_skill
# tool at boot but never actually invokes it — so the aura-skills
# SKILL.md content never reaches the model's context, only the
# TOML system_prompt + skill DESCRIPTIONS in the catalog.
#
# Impact measured: 0-67 (Bedrock variance, no skill content) →
# 100.0 (skill content loaded, agent applies triage discipline).
# Diagnosis wall time: 77 seconds after fault-manifest settle-wait.
#
# Insertion: top of the "## SREGym-specific operational notes"
# section, so it's scoped to the SREGym benchmark and doesn't
# pollute the shared aura-sre-preamble.md.

--- a/config/aura-sregym.toml.template
+++ b/config/aura-sregym.toml.template
@@ ## SREGym-specific operational notes @@
 ## SREGym-specific operational notes

+- **MANDATORY first action** — before any other tool call, invoke
+  `load_skill` with `name="kubernetes-pod-triage"`. This skill contains
+  Kubernetes-specific triage discipline (multi-fault triage-table
+  requirement, recency-weighted ordering, probe-misconfiguration
+  stealth-fault signature, exit-code 137 disambiguation) required for a
+  correct diagnosis on this benchmark. Do NOT begin `exec_read_only_
+  kubectl_cmd` calls until you have called `load_skill` and read the
+  returned SKILL.md content. If you attempt any other tool call first,
+  the harness may terminate your diagnosis before the skill guidance is
+  in your context.
+
 - The user message contains instructions about your stage (DIAGNOSIS or
   MITIGATION). Follow them.
